0so%20in%20and%20with%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20Giles%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20push%20for%20mass%20drone%20manufacturing%20in%20Europe%20isn't%20just%20about%20meeting%20current%20threats.%20It's%20about%20leapfrogging%20into%20the%20technologies%20that%20will%20define%20future%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEurope%20sees%20an%20opportunity%20to%20leapfrog%2C%26quot%3B%20Bego%20said.%20%26quot%3BSmaller%20drones%20are%20much%20cheaper%20than%20a%20lot%20of%20traditional%20weapons%20and%20can%20be%20produced%20much%20more%20quickly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20making%20the%20most%20of%20this%20moment%20requires%20more%20than%20just%20factories.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGetting%20to%20the%20scale%20of%20relevance%20for%20deterrence%20and%20defense%20is%20more%20than%20an%20issue%20of%20defense%20production%2C%26quot%3B%20Skip%20Davis%2C%20a%20senior%20fellow%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20European%20Policy%20Analysis%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20about%20the%20ability%20to%20field%20prototypes%2C%20train%20operators%2C%20revise%20operational%20concepts%2C%20and%20integrate%20drones%20into%20logistics%20and%20manoeuvre%20formations%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BAll%20of%20that%20requires%20a%20new%20mindset.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20would%20involve%20deeper%20collaboration%20between%20militaries%20and%20agile%2C%20often%20non-traditional%20tech%20firms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDavis%20said%20that%20in%20the%20current%20environment%2C%20%26quot%3Bmany%20of%20the%20companies%20leading%20innovation%20are%20small%20startups%20or%20commercial%20companies%20not%20used%20to%20working%20with%20militaries.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Europe%20to%20succeed%2C%20he%20said%20it%20must%20grow%20more%20comfortable%20with%20experimentation%20and%20iteration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompounding%20the%20urgency%20is%20the%20decreasing%20estimate%20of%20when%20Russia%20could%20be%20ready%20to%20attack%20a%20NATO%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20estimate%20of%20five%20years%20was%20what%20we%20were%20hearing%20this%20time%20last%20year%2C%20Giles%20said.%20%26quot%3BSince%20then%2C%20the%20timescale%20has%20continued%20to%20shrink%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20reduction%20in%20US%20support%20to%20Ukraine%20brings%20the%20time%20closer.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20shortening%20horizon%20makes%20the%20EU's%20slow%20progress%20all%20the%20more%20dangerous.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCrash%20rearmament%20is%20feasible%2C%20if%20there%20is%20sufficient%20political%20will%2C%26quot%3B%20Giles%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20experts%20warn%20that%20ramping%20up%20drone%20output%20is%20not%20a%20silver%20bullet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPolicymakers%20are%20at%20risk%20of%20seeing%20small%20agile%20drones%20as%20a%20panacea%20which%20will%20solve%20both%20their%20financial%20and%20manpower%20woes%2C%26quot%3B%20Bego%20said.%20But%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20still%20a%20need%20for%20large%20platforms%20like%20jet%20fighters%2C%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Europe's%20vision%20of%20%26quot%3Bstrategic%20autonomy%26quot%3B%20in%20defense%20risks%20being%20undermined%20by%20its%20reliance%20on%20foreign%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20critical%20components%20in%20drone%20manufacturing%20are%20still%20produced%20in%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20Bego%20said.%20%26quot%3BEurope%20must%20diversify%20these%20supply%20chains%20or%20reproduce%20them%20within%20its%20own%20borders.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20clock%20ticking%20and%20Russian%20production%20accelerating%2C%20the%20EU's%20ambitious%20drone%20target%20looks%20ever%20more%20necessary%2C%20and%20could%20mark%20a%20pivotal%20moment%20in%20European%20defense.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feurope-urged-produce-millions-drones-year-russia-ukraine-war-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3