751547795-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-461614%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20small%20steps%20taken%20to%20provide%20women%20an%20identity%20and%20security%20started%20long%20before%20independence.%20Picture%20Source%3A%20CWDS%20Archives%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E1.%20The%20Hindu%20Widows%E2%80%99%20Remarriage%20Act%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%3A%201856%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%3A%20Across%20British%20India%20for%20Hindus%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201800s%20India%2C%20if%20your%20husband%20died%2C%20society%20expected%20you%20to%20become%20invisible.%20You%20were%20stripped%20of%20colour%2C%20joy%2C%20and%20agency.%20Widows%20were%20considered%20inauspicious%20and%20often%20forced%20into%20a%20life%20of%20isolation%2C%20sometimes%20even%20child%20widows%20as%20young%20as%20eight%20or%20nine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20came%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F182357%2Fishwar-chandra-vidyasagar-widow-remarriage-bengal-women-rights-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIshwar%20Chandra%20Vidyasagar%2C%20a%20reformer%20from%20Bengal%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20refused%20to%20accept%20this%20cruelty%20as%20%E2%80%9Ctradition.%E2%80%9D%20He%20lobbied%20the%20British%2C%20rallied%20public%20opinion%2C%20and%20eventually%20succeeded.%20The%201856%20law%20legally%20allowed%20Hindu%20widows%20to%20remarry%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that%20was%20almost%20unthinkable%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20just%20about%20marriage.%20It%20was%20about%20giving%20women%20a%20second%20chance%20at%20life.%20A%20radical%20concept%20back%20then%20%E2%80%94%20still%20powerful%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E2.%20The%20Married%20Women%E2%80%99s%20Property%20Act%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%3A%201874%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%3A%20British%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20the%20thing%3A%20before%20this%20law%2C%20once%20a%20woman%20got%20married%2C%20anything%20she%20owned%20%E2%80%94%20money%2C%20land%2C%20jewellery%2C%20automatically%20belonged%20to%20her%20husband.%20She%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20sell%20it%2C%20invest%20it%2C%20or%20use%20it%20independently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20Act%20changed%20that.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F185674%2Findia-women-rights-property-inheritance-law-buying%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIt%20legally%20recognised%20a%20married%20woman%E2%80%99s%20right%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20hold%20property%20in%20her%20own%20name.%20She%20could%20now%20have%20legal%20ownership%20over%20her%20earnings%20and%20belongings%2C%20even%20while%20being%20married.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20an%20early%20attempt%20to%20say%3A%20a%20woman%20isn%E2%80%99t%20an%20extension%20of%20her%20husband.%20She%20has%20a%20legal%20identity.%20She%20can%20earn%2C%20own%2C%20and%20control.%20A%20quietly%20radical%20move%20for%20a%20society%20that%20didn%E2%80%99t%20even%20think%20women%20needed%20bank%20accounts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E3.%20The%20Child%20Marriage%20Restraint%20Act%20(Sarda%20Act)%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%3A%201929%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%3A%20All%20of%20British%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChild%20marriage%20was%20not%20just%20common%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20the%20norm.%20Girls%20were%20married%20off%20before%20they%20even%20hit%20puberty.%20The%20Sarda%20Act%2C%20named%20after%20judge%20and%20reformer%20Harbilas%20Sarda%2C%20was%20India%E2%80%99s%20first%20real%20attempt%20to%20put%20an%20age%20limit%20on%20this%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E