%20and%20still%20isn%E2%80%99t%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E4.%20The%20Hindu%20Succession%20Act%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%3A%201956%2C%20Amended%202005%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%3A%20Post-independence%20India%20for%20Hindus%2C%20Buddhists%2C%20Jains%20%26amp%3B%20Sikhs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsk%20any%20woman%20from%20the%20%E2%80%9880s%20or%20%E2%80%9890s%20about%20inheritance%2C%20and%20chances%20are%20she%E2%80%99ll%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CMy%20brother%20got%20everything.%E2%80%9D%20Before%201956%2C%20women%20in%20Hindu%20families%20were%20not%20legal%20heirs%20to%20joint%20family%20property.%20That%20meant%20land%2C%20ancestral%20homes%2C%20and%20farmland%20%E2%80%94%20all%20went%20to%20the%20sons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%201956%20law%20made%20daughters%20legal%20heirs%20for%20the%20first%20time.%20But%20even%20then%2C%20the%20right%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20equal%2C%20especially%20if%20the%20father%20was%20still%20alive.%20It%20was%20only%20with%20the%202005%20amendment%20that%20the%20law%20went%20further%2C%20declaring%20daughters%20as%20coparceners%20%E2%80%94%20equal%20in%20rights%20and%20duties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20plain%20terms%3A%20if%20your%20brother%20gets%20land%2C%20you%20get%20land.%20No%20questions.%20No%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E5.%20The%20Dissolution%20of%20Muslim%20Marriages%20Act%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%3A%201939%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%3A%20British%20India%20(for%20Muslims)%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20one%20is%20often%20overlooked%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20quietly%20one%20of%20the%20most%20empowering.%20It%20gave%20Muslim%20women%20the%20right%20to%20legally%20divorce%20their%20husbands%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that%20was%20historically%20much%20easier%20for%20men%20via%20talaq.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20law%20listed%20specific%20grounds%3A%20cruelty%2C